{
  "stem": "7832.4",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I don't remember whether it was the [? revere ?] in Birkenau or the [? revere ?] in Auschwitz But they were-- they were going-- they told us that they were going to take the number out of our arm.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And Sabka and I said, oh, well, that'll be good.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "At least if we survive, we won't have a reminder that we were here.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And she says, if we survive, and that's all she said.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And then they took us in, and we didn't go back to the barrack after, but they kept us there.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they-- they never gave us an anesthetic.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And there were just the two of us out of the five.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So, again, I don't know what happened to the other three.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I don't know whether they died or they-- they took them somewheres else.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But now, there was only the two of us left.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we were laying on a-- on a rusty table alongside one another, and the doctor and the nurse were between the two of us.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And they were-- first, they were injecting things into our arm, like underneath the-- the-- and that wasn't too bad, because it was just like an injection.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And then they were pulling things out of there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And by then, our arm was swelling and-- and then they were-- and then they were cutting without-- anesthetic.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And-- and within a week, I think, or 10 days, they found a way to get rid of the number.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we didn't know why.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Why would they want to take it out after they put it in, and why us?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Why do they want our number out?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then the nurse that was working with them, she told us that the SS have SS printed under their left arm.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
